IT-JOBS  I agree with the "S tier strategy" in job hunting because it allows candidates to increase their chances of getting hired and build their experience and resume faster. When candidates expand the geographic region in which they are willing to work, they are opening themselves up to a larger pool of opportunities. This means that they are more likely to get hired sooner, and they can also build their experience and resume more quickly. In addition, working in a different geographic region can help candidates build their network. When candidates meet new people in a new city, they are essentially creating connections that can also help them to find their next job. These connections can also help them learn about new opportunities and to get their foot in the door with potential employers.
